The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Tuesday, December 24, 2002 				 SA, Bangla confirm
																								Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board said on Monday it had received written confirmation from South Africa and Bangladesh that they would tour the country next year.																								Foreign teams have, in the recent past, refused to play in Pakistan because of security concerns.																								But the PCB said South Africa and Bangladesh had signalled their willingness to tour from September to November next year, when they are due to play three Tests each and a triangular one-day tournament.																								It is positive news for Pakistan cricket which has suffered a lot,  PCB chairman Lt. Gen Tauqir Zia said. (REUTERS)
